This paper deals with the Memento Framework, which is a web archiving and digital preservation framework. The paper discusses a caching algorithm for TimeMaps, which are machine-readable lists of time-specific copies of an archived original resource. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.CC), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). However, given the focus on web archiving and digital preservation, cs.DL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IR and cs.CR.
